data.meta_description: Former President and 2024 Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump will hold a campaign rally at the Brick Breeden Fieldhouse at Montana State University in Bozeman on Friday, Aug. 9.
data.text:
Former President and 2024 Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump will hold a campaign rally at the Brick Breeden Fieldhouse at Montana State University in Bozeman on Friday, Aug. 9.

The Trump campaign posted details of the rally Thursday. The Aug. 9 event — which aims to bolster Republican Tim Sheehy’s challenge to U.S. Sen. Jon Tester, D-Montana — starts at 8 p.m.

Doors will open at 4 p.m. with tickets available at https://tinyurl.com/2wwdx2zp.

Trump carried Montana by 16 points over President Joe Biden in 2020 and the state is not a presidential battleground in the 2024 race against Vice President Kamala Harris.

Harris has been catapulted to the top of the Democratic ticket after Biden, 81, was pressured out of the race by wealthy party donors and power brokers concerned about his age.

Sheehy is a former Navy SEAL and founder of Belgrade-based Bridger Aerospace. He is looking to unseat Tester — who is seeking a fourth, six-year term — in a race that could determine which party controls the U.S. Senate.

Trump previously endorsed Sheehy over U.S. Rep. Matt Rosendale, R-Montana, in the run-up to the GOP Senate primary.

On July 13, Trump narrowly survived an assassination attempt at an open-air rally in Pennsylvania after a security failure by the U.S. Secret Service allowed a 20-year-old gunman to get on a rough 150 yards from the rally stage and get off 8 shots at Trump.

One bullet hit Trump in the ear. A rally goer was killed and two others injured before a government sniper killed the would-be assassin.
